{"id": 17490, "date": "1987-01-02T11:00:00", "date_gmt": "1987-01-02T19:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=17490"}, "modified": "2026-06-03T16:44:43", "modified_gmt": "2026-06-03T23:44:43", "slug": "matr-bruce-springsteen-and-patti-scialfa-it-takes-two", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1987/01/02/matr-bruce-springsteen-and-patti-scialfa-it-takes-two/", "title": {"rendered": "It Takes Two"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>For all of the countless hours they&#8217;ve shared a stage together, it&#8217;s surprisingly difficult to come across a true duet between Bruce Springsteen and Patti Scialfa.</p>\n<p>You can trip over performances where Patti&#8217;s vocals back her husband&#8217;s, of course&#8211;just pick any E Street Band show since 1984. The converse is a lot rarer, but those performances are out there, too.</p>\n<p>And while on almost any given night on Broadway, theatergoers were treated to lovely intimate Bruce-and-Patti performances of &#8220;Brilliant Disguise&#8221; and &#8220;Tougher Than the Rest,&#8221; these duets were essentially just Patti shadowing Bruce.</p>\n<p>If you want a true trading-vocals duet between Bruce Springsteen and Patti Scialfa, you&#8217;re going to have to look carefully. But at least you don&#8217;t have to look far&#8211;no further than Asbury Park and the annual school benefit concerts and holiday shows where the Jersey Shore&#8217;s first couple made frequent appearances.</p>\n<p>On five of those occasions, Bruce and Patti teamed up on a faithful arrangement of Marvin Gaye and Kim Weston&#8217;s R&amp;B classic, &#8220;It Takes Two.&#8221;</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/cB5sCP6s120?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>&#8220;It Takes Two&#8221; was a huge hit when it was first released, peaking at #4 on the Billboard Soul Singles chart and #14 on the Pop chart in early 1967.</p>\n<p>It clearly made a lasting impression on Bruce&#8211;he featured it nightly on the Reunion Tour as the outro to &#8220;Two Hearts,&#8221; sharing the mic with his lifelong best friend.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/HOLyHZiUkzk?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>But while Bruce has teased us with a snippet of &#8220;It Takes Two&#8221; with Steve more than 150 times over the years, he&#8217;s only performed the entire song five times&#8211;all of them with Patti.</p>\n<p>Unfortunately, four of those five times either weren&#8217;t captured or don&#8217;t circulate.\u00a0 One of them, however, did escape into the wild, and what a wonderful listen it provides.</p>\n<p>On the evening of December 19, 2004, Bruce staged two holiday benefit shows at Harry&#8217;s Roadhouse in Asbury Park, backed by Bobby Bandiera and his band. Patti joined for the late show, and together Bruce and Patti shared a rare spotlight as true partners in a loose (Bruce sounds like he&#8217;s at least a couple of tequillas into the evening), joyful performance of &#8220;It Takes Two.&#8221;</p>\n<div id=\"v-c9grjILs-1\" class=\"video-player\"><iframe title='VideoPress Video Player' aria-label='VideoPress Video Player' width='758' height='426' src='https://videopress.com/embed/c9grjILs?hd=1&amp;cover=1&amp;loop=0&amp;autoPlay=0&amp;permalink=1&amp;muted=0&amp;controls=1&amp;playsinline=0&amp;useAverageColor=0&amp;preloadContent=metadata' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen data-resize-to-parent=\"true\" allow='clipboard-write'></iframe><script data-jetpack-boost=\"ignore\" src='https://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/video/assets/js/next/videopress-iframe.js'></script></div>\n<p><strong>It Takes Two<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> April 13, 2002 (Asbury Park, NJ)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> October 17, 2009 (Asbury Park, NJ)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 April 3, 2020</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>We&#8217;ve seen Patti back Bruce countless times, and Bruce back Patti for at least a few. But rarely do we hear them share a lead vocal, like they did in their wonderful 2004 cover of &#8220;It Takes Two.&#8221;</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 69636, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false}, "categories": [4, 3617, 5], "tags": [2705, 2704, 2437, 115], "class_list": ["p